<TITLE> Arrest warrant out on SQ Chy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 3 (bdnews24.com)  A Chittagong district court on Thursday issued an arrest warrant against senior BNP leader Salauddin Quader Chowdhury in a defamation case. The MP from Chittagong-2 constituency is accused of making provocative and defamatory comments about the 1975 assassination of national hero Sheikh Mujibur Rahman and the Supreme Court's verdict in the murder case last month. Chowdhury reportedly told a local BNP council in Fatikchhari: "Aug 15 is an important day in our national life as the nation was emancipated from one-party rule that day." Regarding the Supreme Court verdict, upholding death sentences of the former officers convicted of the killing, he said: "The nation has not accepted this verdict." A number of newspapers ran stories on the comments made by Chowdhury on Aug 15 and the verdict. Chittagong senior judicial magistrate Akhtar Hossain issued an arrest warrant Thursday against Chowdhury after hearing a case filed the same day by businessman Abu Taher Uddin of Shulkbahar in the port city. The plaintiff's lawyer Ashok Das told bdnews24.com that as an MP Chowdhury should not have made the remarks. "They went against the state and the constitution," he said. "So, he could be charged with sedition," he said. bd
